        <strong><span style="color: #c54c82"> Arepas</span></strong> are a type
        of food made of ground maize dough stuffed with a filling, eaten in
        northern parts of South America since pre-Columbian times, and notable
        primarily in the cuisine of <em>Colombia</em> and <em>Venezuela</em>,
        but also present in Bolivia, Ecuador, and Central America. <br />
        They can have different fillings such as meat, chicken or cheese.
